00:59:46,880 --> 00:59:47,380
[SPEAKER_20]: Thank you, Melissa.

747
00:59:48,260 --> 00:59:53,582
[SPEAKER_00]: To add to that, we are not required when we have a municipal election to send out the vote by mail applications.

748
00:59:54,190 --> 00:59:58,951
[SPEAKER_00]: We did send those out in our census, and we've received about 5,000 vote-by-mail applications.

749
00:59:59,371 --> 01:00:03,312
[SPEAKER_00]: They weren't translated, but that's part of our outreach.

750
01:00:03,352 --> 01:00:07,072
[SPEAKER_00]: It's using creative ways to sort of make sure that we're reaching everybody.

751
01:00:07,092 --> 01:00:07,993
[SPEAKER_13]: Great.

752
01:00:08,033 --> 01:00:14,694
[SPEAKER_00]: There was a brochure in there that was translated to different languages just from the city.

753
01:00:14,734 --> 01:00:16,834
[SPEAKER_00]: It wasn't from any particular department as well.

754
01:00:16,954 --> 01:00:19,995
[SPEAKER_00]: So we're really trying, and we will continue to do so.

755
01:00:20,415 --> 01:00:20,675
[SPEAKER_20]: Great.

756
01:00:20,735 --> 01:00:21,015
[SPEAKER_20]: Thank you.

757
