01:01:00,128 --> 01:01:02,371
[SPEAKER_00]: I just don't know.

767
01:01:02,471 --> 01:01:03,652
[SPEAKER_00]: I mean, I think we would try.

768
01:01:03,672 --> 01:01:06,576
[SPEAKER_00]: Madam Chief of Staff, are you able to address that?

769
01:01:07,437 --> 01:01:07,797
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you.

770
01:01:07,877 --> 01:01:08,478
[SPEAKER_07]: Yes.

771
01:01:10,380 --> 01:01:11,101
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you, Madam President.

772
01:01:11,121 --> 01:01:15,065
[SPEAKER_07]: Yes, I mean, look, if we try to find to begin to say

773
01:01:16,377 --> 01:01:20,099
[SPEAKER_07]: it's important to find the right person to fit the position, right?

774
01:01:20,460 --> 01:01:41,092
[SPEAKER_07]: And if, you know, traditionally the hiring process begins with the department head, especially for, you know, staff directly involved, the department head is involved in that hiring process in this case, and it was evidenced by the hiring process or the, what essentially ended up being the promotion of the senior clerk to the head clerk,

775
01:01:42,343 --> 01:01:47,230
[SPEAKER_07]: department head is involved in that hiring process, and that has an opportunity to make a recommendation.

776
01:01:47,610 --> 01:01:52,537
[SPEAKER_07]: If ultimately the department head doesn't make a recommendation to hire, we would evaluate alternative options.

777
01:01:52,617 --> 01:01:58,505
[SPEAKER_07]: Of course, if the alternatives were we're just not finding the people we need to act reasonably quickly on this matter.

778
01:01:58,865 --> 01:02:00,007
[SPEAKER_07]: So in theory, we would

779
01:02:00,418 --> 01:02:02,219
[SPEAKER_07]: consider coming back to the city council.

780
01:02:02,480 --> 01:02:05,642
[SPEAKER_07]: If we were in that position, we felt there was just no one to be hired.

781
01:02:05,682 --> 01:02:11,326
[SPEAKER_07]: And I'm speaking for myself as what would be my recommendation to the mayor.

782
01:02:11,346 --> 01:02:20,433
[SPEAKER_07]: It would be to come back to the city council, ask for a modified appropriation if that needed to be appropriated from elsewhere, because there was nothing left to raise and appropriate.

783
01:02:20,793 --> 01:02:26,197
[SPEAKER_07]: We would identify an alternative source and attempt to make a modification with the approval of city council, of course.

784
01:02:26,618 --> 01:02:27,358
[SPEAKER_07]: Great, thank you.

785
01:02:28,319 --> 01:02:29,420
[SPEAKER_08]: Any other questions from the council?

786
01:02:31,900 --> 01:02:32,460
[SPEAKER_08]: Thank you so much.

787
01:02:32,601 --> 01:02:33,321
[SPEAKER_08]: Thank you very much.

788
01:02:33,341 --> 01:02:34,722
[SPEAKER_08]: Have a nice evening as well.

789
01:02:34,842 --> 01:02:39,546
[SPEAKER_08]: So we'll take the two smaller departments, then we'll go to police and PDS and round out the board.

790
01:02:39,566 --> 01:02:43,469
[SPEAKER_08]: So we'll go to veterans and then we'll do assessor and then we'll go into the larger department.

