01:02:55,130 --> 01:02:59,795
[SPEAKER_08]: So veteran service department's expenditure summary is $435,703 up $3,372.78 over the prior year and we have Director of Veteran Services Jeremy Johns with us.

793
01:02:59,835 --> 01:03:02,178
[SPEAKER_08]: So any highlights or anything you'd like to share with us?

794
01:03:11,971 --> 01:03:12,731
[SPEAKER_08]: And we'll go to questions.

795
01:03:13,572 --> 01:03:13,792
[SPEAKER_18]: OK.

796
01:03:13,952 --> 01:03:18,013
[SPEAKER_18]: Thank you so much for your time, Madam President.

797
01:03:19,554 --> 01:03:37,640
[SPEAKER_18]: So when I took over last June 13, first started with the Massachusetts Department of Veterans Services, becoming certified with them for the Chapter 115, which is the primary reason for my role, Chapter 115 disbursements for those needy veterans and their dependents.

798
01:03:40,921 --> 01:03:49,126
[SPEAKER_18]: approached the mayor about getting accreditation to be able to touch and deal with Veterans Affairs claims, both pension and disability claims.

799
01:03:49,847 --> 01:03:52,308
[SPEAKER_18]: That is not a normal thing in the state of Massachusetts.

800
01:03:53,269 --> 01:03:59,252
[SPEAKER_18]: The State Department of Veterans Services does not extend that accreditation down to the towns and the cities.

801
01:04:00,073 --> 01:04:06,997
[SPEAKER_18]: Those that you'll see online through the different powers of attorney, like Vietnam Veterans of America or American

802
01:04:08,734 --> 01:04:12,838
[SPEAKER_18]: AMBETS, American Legion, they are independent.

803
01:04:13,799 --> 01:04:20,426
[SPEAKER_18]: So they had to do a 40-hour accreditation with the Department of Veterans Affairs so that they could do these claims.

804
01:04:21,567 --> 01:04:32,738
[SPEAKER_18]: So I got approval to do that with the National Association of County Veterans Service Officers, and now I'm able to look into veterans' claims once they change power of attorney.

805
01:04:33,538 --> 01:04:54,934
[SPEAKER_18]: and help them out with the disability and pension claims DIC claims or dependency indemnity compensation claims, things that they would be if they were on chapter 115, which is a state and city benefit, they might have to be switched then over to federal, which is a benefit so that we could help out others at the chapter 115 level.

806
01:04:55,935 --> 01:04:57,096
[SPEAKER_08]: Okay, thank you.

807
01:05:08,495 --> 01:05:15,145
[SPEAKER_02]: Um, have you seen an increase in people coming into the office since you started?

808
01:05:15,926 --> 01:05:16,367
[SPEAKER_02]: Yes, sir.

809
01:05:16,827 --> 01:05:18,630
[SPEAKER_02]: Especially with the VA claims.

