01:05:18,710 --> 01:05:19,271
[SPEAKER_18]: I'm about to show you.

811
01:05:19,572 --> 01:05:20,072
[SPEAKER_18]: That's my dad.

812
01:05:24,240 --> 01:05:30,102
[SPEAKER_18]: Yes, I've seen an uptick, both with Chapter 115 and with the VA claims.

813
01:05:30,903 --> 01:05:40,226
[SPEAKER_18]: I've always made sure that the Medford residents have priority when it comes down to the appointments that I can offer, but I have seen an uptick in activity.

814
01:05:43,927 --> 01:05:46,788
[SPEAKER_02]: I think I've talked to you about this before.

815
01:05:49,049 --> 01:05:50,830
[SPEAKER_02]: How are you working to bridge that gap?

816
01:05:52,431 --> 01:06:01,154
[SPEAKER_02]: or that big space between the veterans group, from Vietnam, that 20-year share gap, or to the Afghan veterans, the Middle East veterans.

817
01:06:02,054 --> 01:06:08,576
[SPEAKER_02]: Are you starting to see the Middle East guys starting to come in, or are they kind of doing it, you know, trying to go in on their own?

818
01:06:09,178 --> 01:06:15,325
[SPEAKER_18]: I'm actually I've got an appointment tomorrow with a veteran that just left active duty a couple of months ago.

819
01:06:15,465 --> 01:06:24,336
[SPEAKER_18]: I have dealt with a Vietnam veteran that just because I was able to look through his claim, see where the error was, went through a higher level review, now he's at 100%.

820
01:06:29,456 --> 01:06:33,182
[SPEAKER_18]: Bridging the gap, I would like to say would be finding a good communication.

821
01:06:33,202 --> 01:06:38,751
[SPEAKER_18]: We used to have a newspaper and I'm sure that that's where most people got their information for the city.

822
01:06:39,852 --> 01:06:40,353
[SPEAKER_18]: We've got.

823
01:06:42,192 --> 01:06:59,616
[SPEAKER_18]: several Facebook web pages for the city of Medford, and then people that create their own under the city of Medford guys so I try to follow some of those and see if we can use that as a, as a push for information, but like the the non service connected pension and then chapter one 15 benefits.

824
01:07:00,856 --> 01:07:04,237
[SPEAKER_18]: Those are a lot of them are elderly, those that are disabled can't work.

825
01:07:04,777 --> 01:07:06,638
[SPEAKER_18]: they don't have computers, they don't have internet.

826
01:07:07,298 --> 01:07:18,001
[SPEAKER_18]: And so it's, I just discovered this, the new free, the free newspaper that is for Somerville and Bedford, potentially advertising in there.

827
01:07:18,621 --> 01:07:24,023
[SPEAKER_18]: I go to the senior center with the first pamphlets that I have for the requirements for chapter 115.

828
01:07:24,123 --> 01:07:34,106
[SPEAKER_18]: I can do a little, maybe more outreach at the emergency rooms at the hospital to kind of put that out, but there's a different,

829
01:07:35,882 --> 01:07:39,984
[SPEAKER_18]: It's hard to say where the majority of Medford residents get their information.

830
01:07:40,004 --> 01:07:41,504
[SPEAKER_18]: If I could find that out.

831
01:07:42,324 --> 01:07:44,865
[SPEAKER_02]: Are you notified when a veteran moves into the community?

832
01:07:45,486 --> 01:07:46,446
[SPEAKER_18]: I am through the state.

833
01:07:46,466 --> 01:07:47,006
[SPEAKER_18]: Okay.

834
01:07:47,246 --> 01:07:47,826
[SPEAKER_18]: I get a list.

835
01:07:48,207 --> 01:07:55,009
[SPEAKER_18]: And then I send out a letter saying you could be qualified for the welcome back bonus.

836
01:07:55,749 --> 01:08:02,572
[SPEAKER_18]: If the person is 100% service connected, they also get a annuity from the state twice a year.

837
01:08:02,592 --> 01:08:04,893
[SPEAKER_18]: I wanna make sure that they stay informed on that.

838
01:08:05,753 --> 01:08:07,594
[SPEAKER_18]: Yes, I also welcome them to Medford with a letter.

839
01:08:08,194 --> 01:08:11,216
[SPEAKER_02]: Do we do mailings to the veterans that we know live in the city?

840
01:08:11,716 --> 01:08:12,157
[SPEAKER_02]: Yes, we do.

841
01:08:12,977 --> 01:08:14,218
[SPEAKER_02]: And their spouses also?

842
01:08:18,053 --> 01:08:25,057
[SPEAKER_18]: If they're identified through the state, if they're new into the community, other than that, it typically is just the veteran.

843
01:08:26,117 --> 01:08:30,180
[SPEAKER_18]: I don't know the veteran's marital status or who they've moved in with.

844
01:08:30,580 --> 01:08:37,984
[SPEAKER_18]: It's just if a veteran has left active duty or has returned from basic AIT, basic training, if they're in the National Guard.

845
01:08:38,024 --> 01:08:39,605
[SPEAKER_18]: That's how I get that information.

846
01:08:39,885 --> 01:08:44,948
[SPEAKER_02]: It'd be nice when a new veteran moves into the community, if we could send them a welcome letter or some kind of welcome package.

847
01:08:45,508 --> 01:08:47,729
[SPEAKER_02]: saying, you know, we're here to help.

848
01:08:48,189 --> 01:08:48,990
[SPEAKER_18]: Oh, yeah, absolutely.

849
01:08:49,170 --> 01:08:49,610
[SPEAKER_18]: Absolutely.

850
01:08:49,630 --> 01:08:58,594
[SPEAKER_18]: We do that with the letter also try to make sure that they understand what services are offered at the office as well, and show some of the unique aspects that I can offer them.

851
01:08:58,894 --> 01:08:59,174
[SPEAKER_18]: Yes, sir.

852
01:08:59,194 --> 01:08:59,795
[SPEAKER_18]: Thank you.

853
01:09:04,905 --> 01:09:05,686
[SPEAKER_20]: Thank you, Madam President.

854
01:09:05,786 --> 01:09:06,746
[SPEAKER_20]: Thanks, Jeremy.

855
01:09:07,407 --> 01:09:15,772
[SPEAKER_20]: Sorry for cracking up when you said Facebook groups, but the state of public discourse and the level of good information that is out there in the community is wanting.

856
01:09:16,812 --> 01:09:18,734
[SPEAKER_20]: I only have one question for you.

857
01:09:18,754 --> 01:09:23,217
[SPEAKER_20]: Other than that, unless you want to found a newspaper, that'd be much appreciated.

858
01:09:24,797 --> 01:09:28,560
[SPEAKER_20]: Is there anything that you are looking for that you may be requested

859
01:09:29,140 --> 01:09:36,343
[SPEAKER_20]: for this year that you weren't able to get or anything in the future that your office really needs in terms of resources or staffing to do more?

860
01:09:42,922 --> 01:09:45,563
[SPEAKER_18]: Currently, I'm satisfied with what had been agreed upon.

861
01:09:46,603 --> 01:10:02,509
[SPEAKER_18]: When it comes down to the cash aid that we have, which is $300,000, I'm not able to predict when a qualified veteran comes in and requests to file for Chapter 115 or I'm able to identify them as somebody that could receive that benefit.

862
01:10:05,210 --> 01:10:12,794
[SPEAKER_18]: If the economy were to do a downturn, something like that, we would end up going currently right now to get up 22 recipients on Chapter 115.

863
01:10:15,014 --> 01:10:19,176
[SPEAKER_18]: Looking through the history, we were up to almost 40 at one point in time with COVID.

864
01:10:22,398 --> 01:10:35,467
[SPEAKER_18]: That way, the 300,000, as long as it covers that, then I wouldn't have to ask for funding in the midterm point, but I can't predict when the number would increase of need.

865
01:10:36,227 --> 01:10:47,655
[SPEAKER_20]: Now, just for my clarification, it's a fixed benefit amount, so we would run out, or the amount is divided among the beneficiaries equally?

866
01:10:49,293 --> 01:10:50,134
[SPEAKER_18]: somewhat like that.

867
01:10:50,254 --> 01:11:09,845
[SPEAKER_18]: So depending on the person that's coming in, um, if they have out of pocket medical expenses, if they're not, if they're paying for their, their, uh, Medicare part B, we can reimburse that as long as they meet that the asset financial requirement, they of course have to be an honorably discharged veteran or an unmarried dependent spouse.

868
01:11:10,225 --> 01:11:13,667
[SPEAKER_18]: Um, but I have a family that I've pay out,

869
01:11:16,622 --> 01:11:18,143
[SPEAKER_18]: $1,600 a month right now.

870
01:11:18,423 --> 01:11:23,227
[SPEAKER_18]: And then I have some that are maybe just getting, the one lady was getting $98.

871
01:11:23,267 --> 01:11:26,630
[SPEAKER_18]: So it's a variable depending on their need.

872
01:11:26,890 --> 01:11:32,414
[SPEAKER_20]: But we're covering it now, but in an economic downturn, there'd be more people who qualify and need it, and we wouldn't be able to get there.

873
01:11:32,915 --> 01:11:33,235
[SPEAKER_18]: Correct.

874
01:11:33,435 --> 01:11:37,739
[SPEAKER_18]: Now, the city does not get reimbursed 25% of every dollar that goes out.

875
01:11:37,779 --> 01:11:39,300
[SPEAKER_18]: That does come from the city.

876
01:11:39,320 --> 01:11:43,763
[SPEAKER_18]: 75% is reimbursed from the state of Massachusetts, and we see that.

877
01:11:44,984 --> 01:11:46,486
[SPEAKER_18]: when we close the months out.

878
01:11:46,706 --> 01:11:46,947
[SPEAKER_18]: Okay.

879
01:11:47,167 --> 01:11:47,487
[SPEAKER_18]: Thank you.

880
01:11:47,948 --> 01:11:49,289
[SPEAKER_18]: Appreciate your work.

881
01:11:49,330 --> 01:12:02,565
[SPEAKER_18]: I was able to also, from last year's budget, I did need software as well as the accreditation for the VA claims and that's where there would have been an increase in expenditures.

882
01:12:03,066 --> 01:12:03,286
[SPEAKER_18]: Great.

883
01:12:03,506 --> 01:12:03,786
[SPEAKER_18]: Thank you.

884
01:12:04,895 --> 01:12:05,495
[SPEAKER_08]: Councilor Scarpa.

885
01:12:06,296 --> 01:12:07,056
[SPEAKER_15]: Thank you, Madam President.

886
01:12:07,717 --> 01:12:08,497
[SPEAKER_15]: Thank you, Mr. Johns.

887
01:12:08,537 --> 01:12:16,442
[SPEAKER_15]: I know this is a very vital position here in the city, and we know how important you are, so we appreciate all your hard work.

888
01:12:16,942 --> 01:12:21,504
[SPEAKER_15]: Staffing levels, do you find it adequate within your department?

889
01:12:21,965 --> 01:12:22,945
[SPEAKER_15]: Depending on the day, yes.

890
01:12:23,606 --> 01:12:25,947
[SPEAKER_15]: Do you have a full-time

