1104
01:28:15,303 --> 01:28:20,586
[SPEAKER_01]: On a more macro level, yeah, that's on us to make sure we have fair and equitable valuation of property.

1105
01:28:21,887 --> 01:28:23,828
[SPEAKER_01]: People don't understand a lot of times that it trails.

1106
01:28:24,268 --> 01:28:29,430
[SPEAKER_01]: The lien dates from the last January 1st, so it trails up to 18 months.

1107
01:28:30,231 --> 01:28:32,892
[SPEAKER_01]: Our assessment to sales ratios are usually around 0.93.

1108
01:28:36,474 --> 01:28:43,338
[SPEAKER_01]: a lot of factors that go into why the valuation that we have might not be exactly what they think is an appraisal value.

1109
01:28:43,358 --> 01:28:44,739
[SPEAKER_20]: Yeah.

1110
01:28:44,819 --> 01:28:47,321
[SPEAKER_20]: And it's not even the appraisal value piece because that makes sense.

1111
01:28:47,341 --> 01:28:47,421
[SPEAKER_20]: It's

1112
01:28:49,810 --> 01:28:58,377
[SPEAKER_20]: My understanding of it is essentially you go around every five years, you re-evaluate every property, and then in the interim years, if I get it wrong, correct me immediately.

1113
01:28:58,938 --> 01:28:59,798
[SPEAKER_01]: It still runs 10 years.

1114
01:28:59,839 --> 01:29:04,402
[SPEAKER_01]: We do try to hold more often than that, but yeah, it's by state law every 10 years.

1115
01:29:04,522 --> 01:29:14,171
[SPEAKER_20]: And in the interim, it's basically based on the conditions that we have on your property card, where you're going to be using the sales prices of similar properties to adjust your value.

1116
01:29:14,900 --> 01:29:17,021
[SPEAKER_01]: Yeah, it's a it's a modified cost approach.

1117
01:29:17,041 --> 01:29:19,802
[SPEAKER_01]: So we are using those sales to inform our cost approach.

1118
01:29:19,842 --> 01:29:20,002
[SPEAKER_01]: Yep.

1119
01:29:20,122 --> 01:29:20,362
[SPEAKER_20]: Right.

1120
01:29:20,462 --> 01:29:20,842
[SPEAKER_01]: Exactly.

1121
