01:42:14,230 --> 01:42:15,331
[SPEAKER_15]: Chief, again,

1276
01:42:16,389 --> 01:42:22,854
[SPEAKER_15]: Um, year after year, during the toughest times, you've always, uh, you and your officers have always stood above it all.

1277
01:42:22,934 --> 01:42:28,278
[SPEAKER_15]: So I appreciate your professionalism and your commitment to Medford, my friend.

1278
01:42:28,318 --> 01:42:33,662
[SPEAKER_15]: I think that we are very fortunate to have you as our chief, uh, and have the staff that you do have.

1279
01:42:34,502 --> 01:42:36,883
[SPEAKER_15]: appreciate, you know, the focus on mental health.

1280
01:42:36,963 --> 01:42:38,063
[SPEAKER_15]: That was one of my questions.

1281
01:42:38,143 --> 01:42:40,864
[SPEAKER_15]: But it's it's evident what you're doing.

1282
01:42:40,884 --> 01:42:45,206
[SPEAKER_15]: You listen to some concerns that I wish the rest of the nation listened to.

1283
01:42:45,806 --> 01:42:54,669
[SPEAKER_15]: And methods way ahead of the curve when you know your your offices are are prepared with a mental health professional.

1284
01:42:54,709 --> 01:42:55,609
[SPEAKER_15]: I think that's amazing.

1285
01:42:55,709 --> 01:42:56,650
[SPEAKER_15]: I think it's so important.

1286
01:42:57,250 --> 01:43:00,431
[SPEAKER_15]: I think that we went through a very difficult time back in December and

1287
01:43:00,971 --> 01:43:05,472
[SPEAKER_15]: before with a couple of very, very dangerous issues at Medford High School.

1288
01:43:06,152 --> 01:43:13,214
[SPEAKER_15]: And there's been a lot of talk both nationally and locally about the importance of student resource offices in the in the building.

1289
01:43:14,514 --> 01:43:20,956
[SPEAKER_15]: Whether it's with with the uniforms or street clothes, I think that when you talk to the kids,

1290
01:43:22,252 --> 01:43:35,196
[SPEAKER_15]: forget about what party you belong to, forget about the talk shows, forget about who's fighting for what, what kind of leverage one group wants the other.

1291
01:43:35,716 --> 01:43:38,557
[SPEAKER_15]: When you talk to the kids, and that's what I do, that's my life.

1292
01:43:39,177 --> 01:43:44,239
[SPEAKER_15]: When I talk to the kids, the kids feel safe when there's a police officer in the building.

1293
01:43:44,739 --> 01:43:50,821
[SPEAKER_15]: I think that there's a huge disconnect with communities that don't allow that partnership to occur.

1294
01:43:52,045 --> 01:43:52,725
[SPEAKER_15]: It's direct.

1295
01:43:52,786 --> 01:43:56,868
[SPEAKER_15]: You see direct negative issues in your community when that happens.

1296
01:43:57,989 --> 01:44:01,891
[SPEAKER_15]: And I think that neighbor communities are doing that, and I think it's sad.

1297
01:44:02,212 --> 01:44:14,700
[SPEAKER_15]: I think that we're very fortunate that you stand strong in what your beliefs are, and you share that with the council and the city and appreciate your team for doing that.

1298
01:44:14,780 --> 01:44:16,121
[SPEAKER_15]: I think it's important.

1299
01:44:16,881 --> 01:44:18,182
[SPEAKER_15]: And I think we need to continue that.

1300
01:44:20,490 --> 01:44:32,415
[SPEAKER_15]: you know, when, especially when you have newer people coming to the city, especially moving in for more urban communities, their outlook and their view of police officers are totally different, unfortunately.

1301
01:44:33,135 --> 01:44:49,082
[SPEAKER_15]: But when you see a Memphis police officer, when you have officers initiating national night out, because in other communities, that's initiated by different groups that want to come in and, you know, share their story.

1302
01:44:50,017 --> 01:44:56,081
[SPEAKER_15]: But here in Medford, our police, like you said, our staff, our patrolman really stepped up.

1303
01:44:56,202 --> 01:45:00,365
[SPEAKER_15]: Our lieutenants, our captains, our sergeants said, let's do this.

1304
01:45:00,625 --> 01:45:06,169
[SPEAKER_15]: And you could see the impact if you just drive by the event, let alone walk around the event.

1305
01:45:06,229 --> 01:45:07,670
[SPEAKER_15]: And you just hear people

1306
01:45:09,498 --> 01:45:20,065
[SPEAKER_15]: You even hear, you even see the most negative police proponents that they're even looking at situations like this, and you have to applaud it.

1307
01:45:20,265 --> 01:45:25,149
[SPEAKER_15]: And I think that, for one, I appreciate the police department and what you do.

1308
01:45:25,329 --> 01:45:35,456
[SPEAKER_15]: It's not, you know, especially in a time when it could be very volatile, you personally and your staff, your team, have been very understanding of what

1309
01:45:36,161 --> 01:45:40,442
[SPEAKER_15]: the national trends are and the concerns that we hear, and you're in front of it.

1310
01:45:40,802 --> 01:45:42,742
[SPEAKER_15]: And that's what I really appreciate with your chief.

1311
01:45:44,163 --> 01:45:55,625
[SPEAKER_15]: But when it comes to the budget, I think there are some things that, you know, some of old Malden Everett, neighbor communities to a program and I do it with partnership with our PD, some recreation.

1312
01:45:56,225 --> 01:45:57,645
[SPEAKER_15]: I think it's an amazing program.

1313
01:45:57,685 --> 01:46:00,146
[SPEAKER_15]: And I want to volunteer and work with Kevin.

1314
01:46:00,754 --> 01:46:06,122
[SPEAKER_15]: and hopefully try to bring the Junior Police Academy here in Metro like we do in the neighborhood communities.

1315
01:46:06,703 --> 01:46:14,995
[SPEAKER_15]: I think it's such an amazing program where you could tap into principals and talk to them about middle schoolers at risk.

1316
01:46:15,876 --> 01:46:31,142
[SPEAKER_15]: and needing that support, especially with childcare, but using it with the people that might be on the gang spectrum and bringing them and and then you realize when that police officer takes off that that that uniform and they weren't shorts and a t shirt.

1317
01:46:32,332 --> 01:46:33,113
[SPEAKER_15]: They're just like them.

1318
01:46:33,133 --> 01:46:38,818
[SPEAKER_15]: And then when they put that jersey back on and they put that badge back on, they realize they're the same people.

1319
01:46:39,478 --> 01:46:43,402
[SPEAKER_15]: And that's the difference that we've seen in our community and in neighboring communities.

1320
01:46:43,462 --> 01:46:51,670
[SPEAKER_15]: When you have 50 kids for a two-week period, 50 different kids each week, you really see the effect and how it just trickles up.

1321
01:46:52,310 --> 01:47:02,255
[SPEAKER_15]: where it's one kid in a group or a gang that has a different outlook on what a police officer is, and how important they are to them as their benefit.

1322
01:47:02,755 --> 01:47:03,756
[SPEAKER_15]: I think it's invaluable.

1323
01:47:03,796 --> 01:47:06,517
[SPEAKER_15]: So that's something I'd like to talk to you later on.

1324
01:47:06,537 --> 01:47:08,918
[SPEAKER_15]: I know the summer's too short, but it's too late.

1325
01:47:08,958 --> 01:47:12,620
[SPEAKER_15]: But maybe even working on something, it's not a very big budget ask.

1326
01:47:12,740 --> 01:47:15,482
[SPEAKER_15]: All it is, is, you know, we do with some of the PDs,

1327
01:47:16,483 --> 01:47:28,773
[SPEAKER_15]: We have a list of officers that are comp sometime, and they'll donate half and they'll comp half, and the deputy chief there and the chief of police, they're all in, and I'm sure you would be too.

1328
01:47:28,833 --> 01:47:33,717
[SPEAKER_15]: So I'm gonna be bothering you with that down the line, because I think it is an important piece.

1329
01:47:34,397 --> 01:47:42,644
[SPEAKER_15]: My two biggest things that I see that's scary in the budget, and we've been here a while, but when you look at patrolmen and women that we're down to,

1330
01:47:44,794 --> 01:48:00,461
[SPEAKER_15]: It looks like 73, and that's not saying that we have 73 on the street, because I know we have, you know, different situations when it comes to injury or when it comes to, you know, paternity maternity leave so I know that's not a true number.

1331
01:48:03,217 --> 01:48:06,339
[SPEAKER_15]: How far under are we with our staffing?

1332
01:48:07,059 --> 01:48:13,883
[SPEAKER_17]: So first off, thank you for the comments and the positive and we will continue to kind of work through that with that community outreach.

1333
01:48:14,283 --> 01:48:23,709
[SPEAKER_17]: I will tell you sneak preview there is a group already talking about, you know, whether it's a junior officer camp or a summer camp for that's very coordinate with all those things.

1334
01:48:24,089 --> 01:48:24,669
[SPEAKER_17]: and jump in there.

1335
01:48:25,330 --> 01:48:29,713
[SPEAKER_17]: Lastly, it's no surprise when it comes to that, but I am a proponent of school resource offices.

1336
01:48:29,773 --> 01:48:30,733
[SPEAKER_17]: I think they're invaluable.

1337
01:48:30,793 --> 01:48:34,396
[SPEAKER_17]: I think it's important for the students to interact with, and we have a great team.

1338
01:48:34,456 --> 01:48:35,296
[SPEAKER_17]: You do have a great team.

1339
01:48:35,316 --> 01:48:35,537
[SPEAKER_17]: We do.

1340
01:48:35,677 --> 01:48:44,642
[SPEAKER_17]: And so I thank them for their work, and we'll continue to kind of push and show that we can do the right things up there.

1341
01:48:44,743 --> 01:48:48,905
[SPEAKER_17]: And we know when to get involved, and we know when not to get involved in the development.

1342
01:48:49,986 --> 01:48:51,087
[SPEAKER_17]: As for staffing, you know,

1343
01:48:52,330 --> 01:48:53,170
[SPEAKER_17]: we're getting back up there.

1344
01:48:53,191 --> 01:49:00,955
[SPEAKER_17]: There'll be a new civil service police list really released in July, and I say that because it's important because.

1345
01:49:00,975 --> 01:49:01,976
[SPEAKER_17]: You know, we're really

1346
01:49:22,114 --> 01:49:26,557
[SPEAKER_17]: We don't get as many people signing up to the civil service process to take the list.

1347
01:49:26,597 --> 01:49:29,819
[SPEAKER_17]: And then when we go through it, the quality is not what we need.

1348
01:49:29,859 --> 01:49:35,963
[SPEAKER_17]: And at this point in time, and probably for the rest of my career, I really refuse to lower the standards because the job is just too tough.

1349
01:49:36,563 --> 01:49:39,065
[SPEAKER_17]: So last year, I think we tried a high of 16.

1350
01:49:39,305 --> 01:49:40,225
[SPEAKER_17]: We were able to get 9, 10.

1351
01:49:42,046 --> 01:49:43,227
[SPEAKER_17]: This year, we're looking at 6.

1352
01:49:43,988 --> 01:49:46,409
[SPEAKER_17]: I'm hoping we can keep that because it's very tight.

1353
01:49:47,870 --> 01:49:58,797
[SPEAKER_17]: You don't have a short window of time to get a lot of things done to hire qualified and competent police officers, but we have significant failure rates when it comes to things like physical fitness and everything.

1354
01:49:58,837 --> 01:49:59,877
[SPEAKER_17]: So we have to buy it.

1355
01:49:59,937 --> 01:50:04,480
[SPEAKER_17]: You get some really good candidates and next thing you know, they can't pass the entrance test to the academies and we're losing.

1356
01:50:05,040 --> 01:50:12,145
[SPEAKER_17]: So, you know, if we get these six to the academy, we're looking really strong up to a 102.

1357
01:50:12,245 --> 01:50:15,267
[SPEAKER_17]: I hope to push and get more right up to the July, but

1358
01:50:16,720 --> 01:50:17,281
[SPEAKER_17]: the fed

1359
01:50:27,649 --> 01:50:30,491
[SPEAKER_17]: We can't just lower our standards because then I don't disagree.

1360
01:50:30,831 --> 01:50:35,174
[SPEAKER_15]: I see some communities that are doing that and it's not looking good.

1361
01:50:35,234 --> 01:50:48,764
[SPEAKER_15]: So the other piece that I have, Chief, thank you for answering that, but it's, you know, our cruisers, I know that people don't realize that, you know, not like your own personal automobile, our cruisers run 24-7.

1362
01:50:50,285 --> 01:50:56,567
[SPEAKER_15]: And so even if it says 2018, it's really double that or triple that because of what they use.

1363
01:50:56,607 --> 01:50:58,387
[SPEAKER_15]: So how do we stand with that fleet?

1364
01:51:00,208 --> 01:51:03,168
[SPEAKER_17]: So it's looking really strong right now.

1365
01:51:03,268 --> 01:51:16,912
[SPEAKER_17]: We have, and the reason for that is the influx of cruises that are coming and there's been some delays, but we expect to have three hybrid police cruises

1366
01:51:17,932 --> 01:51:24,955
[SPEAKER_17]: end of June, and then Mike Wenzel is probably cringing right now because I'm putting an extra thing, and then three more hybrid cruises by the end of July.

1367
01:51:24,975 --> 01:51:25,976
[SPEAKER_17]: So that's a total of six.

1368
01:51:26,256 --> 01:51:33,099
[SPEAKER_17]: Plus, the casino grant has provided us with a pickup truck for a traffic unit that should be coming in somewhere around the same time.

1369
01:51:33,639 --> 01:51:35,860
[SPEAKER_17]: So it's an increase of seven vehicles to the fleet and

1370
01:51:36,620 --> 01:51:38,600
[SPEAKER_17]: you know, this summer, the next couple of months.

1371
01:51:39,801 --> 01:51:52,043
[SPEAKER_17]: And then, you know, we've been working closely with the administration on the capital improvement side of things to kind of ensure that the future is bright and we get some sort of regular production of vehicles to the fleet.

1372
01:51:52,223 --> 01:52:03,625
[SPEAKER_17]: And we are moving on a hybrid, sort of, and everybody is, and we've seen those vehicles, we've tested them, and we're very, you know, happy and confident that all that will work, all the way from the fuel gas models.

1373
01:52:05,579 --> 01:52:12,664
[SPEAKER_15]: We've gone a long way from holes in the floor of most of our patrol cars and, you know, looking at two, two years.

1374
01:52:12,685 --> 01:52:15,106
[SPEAKER_15]: So this is a great, great news in my eyes.

1375
01:52:15,206 --> 01:52:17,388
[SPEAKER_15]: And again, I appreciate all you have.

1376
01:52:17,448 --> 01:52:17,768
[SPEAKER_15]: Thank you.

1377
01:52:17,808 --> 01:52:19,570
[SPEAKER_15]: I appreciate it.

1378
01:52:21,431 --> 01:52:22,172
[SPEAKER_04]: Thank you.

1379
01:52:22,432 --> 01:52:23,093
[SPEAKER_17]: I'm glad you're next.

1380
01:52:23,153 --> 01:52:24,654
[SPEAKER_17]: Cause I feel like I'm always looking over here.

1381
01:52:25,414 --> 01:52:26,275
[SPEAKER_05]: Well, now's your chance.

1382
01:52:26,395 --> 01:52:27,616
[SPEAKER_05]: Well, thank you for being here.

1383
01:52:27,656 --> 01:52:28,517
[SPEAKER_05]: Always good to see you.

1384
01:52:28,837 --> 01:52:28,997
[SPEAKER_05]: Um,

1385
01:52:32,399 --> 01:52:37,102
[SPEAKER_05]: Just one question for you about grant funding sources not included in this budget.

1386
01:52:37,122 --> 01:52:40,364
[SPEAKER_05]: I heard you mention the casino grant for the pickup truck.

1387
01:52:40,384 --> 01:52:44,426
[SPEAKER_05]: I had heard over the weekend about the Cummings grant for community engagement, which is nice to hear.

1388
01:52:44,766 --> 01:52:47,428
[SPEAKER_05]: Are there any other major sources of grant funding that are augmenting your budget?

1389
01:52:47,788 --> 01:52:51,489
[SPEAKER_17]: So there's a MRS grant that we work on, it's traffic safety.

1390
01:52:51,949 --> 01:52:54,550
[SPEAKER_17]: We were the recipient of that public safety grant.

1391
01:52:55,310 --> 01:53:03,673
[SPEAKER_17]: And that is, you know, every month this Commonwealth of Massachusetts comes out with like say a seatbelt campaign or an anti, you know, no texting campaign or speeding campaign.

1392
01:53:04,313 --> 01:53:13,316
[SPEAKER_17]: And they were able to provide extra resources for traffic to get out there and kind of a large part of that program is educational and getting out there and trying to

1393
01:53:15,124 --> 01:53:18,629
[SPEAKER_17]: probably not a surprise to many of you, but the roads are a little crazy these days, right?

1394
01:53:18,689 --> 01:53:26,679
[SPEAKER_17]: And I do think that is one thing I can positively tell you came from the pandemic, very few people on the road and people decided to kind of like, let's pick up the speed and let's try it.

1395
01:53:27,320 --> 01:53:31,266
[SPEAKER_17]: But unfortunately, traffic fatalities are up around the areas.

1396
01:53:32,547 --> 01:53:33,748
[SPEAKER_17]: We had one again this weekend.

1397
01:53:33,988 --> 01:53:39,670
[SPEAKER_17]: And so I think it's valuable to have those sort of educational traffic grants out there.

1398
01:53:39,730 --> 01:53:42,731
[SPEAKER_17]: And so the Commonwealth was happy enough to award us with that program.

1399
01:53:43,552 --> 01:53:52,735
[SPEAKER_17]: And of course, a lot of, you know, we get a state 9-1-1 grant that allows us to do a lot of things internally with 9-1-1 communications.

1400
01:53:53,095 --> 01:53:57,097
[SPEAKER_17]: And there's a lot of training that goes with that that we're able to supplement when it comes to that.

1401
01:53:57,517 --> 01:54:01,339
[SPEAKER_17]: So off the top of my head, I think that's, I don't think I'm missing one.

1402
01:54:02,218 --> 01:54:03,699
[SPEAKER_17]: I don't think I'm missing another grant.

1403
01:54:03,759 --> 01:54:05,481
[SPEAKER_17]: I was just trying to think if there was another one that I missed.

1404
01:54:05,721 --> 01:54:06,141
[SPEAKER_05]: Great, thank you.

1405
01:54:06,161 --> 01:54:07,783
[SPEAKER_05]: So I heard MRS state 9-1-1 grant.

1406
01:54:07,843 --> 01:54:08,883
[SPEAKER_05]: Is that what you said?

1407
01:54:09,164 --> 01:54:17,710
[SPEAKER_17]: Yep, and then the Cummings grant is now available that will be kicking in for us.

1408
01:54:18,971 --> 01:54:19,712
[SPEAKER_17]: We're getting there, right?

1409
01:54:19,732 --> 01:54:25,956
[SPEAKER_17]: We're trying to work on more grants to kind of help fund the police department to supplement it, but not always easy to get.

1410
01:54:26,337 --> 01:54:27,277
[SPEAKER_04]: Yeah, I know that's true.

1411
01:54:27,518 --> 01:54:27,998
[SPEAKER_04]: Thank you very much.

1412
01:54:28,258 --> 01:54:28,458
[SPEAKER_20]: Thanks.

1413
01:54:31,868 --> 01:54:32,529
[SPEAKER_20]: Thank you, Madam President.

1414
01:54:32,549 --> 01:54:33,429
[SPEAKER_20]: Thanks, Chief.

1415
01:54:33,630 --> 01:54:45,161
[SPEAKER_20]: Appreciate the intentional approach around the body camera policy, body-worn camera policy, and generally intentional approaches on many things from you and your team.

1416
