1469
01:58:12,853 --> 01:58:16,094
[SPEAKER_17]: And, and, uh, you know, our reports are up significantly, right.

1470
01:58:16,114 --> 01:58:20,255
[SPEAKER_17]: You know, that, that kind of follow with us and a lot of followup support reports also.

1471
01:58:20,475 --> 01:58:20,716
[SPEAKER_17]: And, um,

1472
01:58:24,916 --> 01:58:40,525
[SPEAKER_17]: I mean, I guess maybe we could kind of look at that and see what those sort of rates, you divide 100 by 40,000, or it's not that easy of a math, because it's, you know, you have a certain group of patrol officers all the time, and not every one of my staff is out on active patrol, and they are the ones who are responding to those 40,000.

1473
01:58:40,605 --> 01:58:48,289
[SPEAKER_20]: Right, and that's why, you know, it may be easy for me to say, oh, we have this 40,000, we have this 73, but there's probably more nuance to it, and that's why I was wondering.

1474
01:58:48,309 --> 01:58:52,211
[SPEAKER_17]: Yeah, and there's a nuance, and of course, you know, some calls are really easy, and some calls take a long time.

1475
01:58:54,153 --> 01:58:55,625
[SPEAKER_17]: you know, we get it done.

1476
01:58:57,364 --> 01:59:04,905
[SPEAKER_17]: 25 years ago when I came to this job, it was from day one, there was changes and moving, changes and moving, and you just had to kind of keep getting the work done and you do it.

1477
01:59:05,085 --> 01:59:18,528
[SPEAKER_17]: And that's why I really, you know, I know I wear the uniform and I know I'm kind of biased and partial towards police, but this police department, they do a lot of really hard work and they don't, you know, they just keep plugging away.

1478
01:59:18,908 --> 01:59:24,129
[SPEAKER_17]: Think about trying to go to work every night at midnight, nights and weekends, and you know, hey,

1479
01:59:25,442 --> 01:59:27,143
[SPEAKER_17]: It's hard, and I understand it.

1480
01:59:27,463 --> 01:59:30,205
[SPEAKER_17]: It gets some of the police officers down.

1481
01:59:30,545 --> 01:59:35,207
[SPEAKER_17]: I got to work overnight again, or I got to work this weekend, and I wanted to be off with my family.

1482
01:59:35,247 --> 01:59:37,749
[SPEAKER_17]: But it's a calling that we chose.

1483
01:59:37,769 --> 01:59:40,510
[SPEAKER_17]: It's a job that we chose because the communities need it.

1484
01:59:40,570 --> 01:59:43,252
[SPEAKER_17]: Christmas night, we've got to be out there, and we know that.

1485
01:59:43,312 --> 01:59:49,055
[SPEAKER_17]: And so that weight gets distributed, and that's why I hold all these guys.

1486
01:59:49,115 --> 01:59:51,336
[SPEAKER_17]: Even when they complain about it, I hold them because I get it.

1487
01:59:51,696 --> 01:59:52,557
[SPEAKER_17]: And I did it one time.

1488
01:59:52,577 --> 01:59:53,597
[SPEAKER_17]: It was tough.

1489
01:59:54,927 --> 02:00:13,544
[SPEAKER_17]: I'm telling you, when you are sitting there, and I'm probably going down a different direction, but when you're sitting there in a cruiser, and it's 3 o'clock in the morning on Christmas morning, and you're praying your two little girls stay asleep before Santa Claus comes, you've got to get your butt home, right?

1490
02:00:13,684 --> 02:00:18,769
[SPEAKER_17]: And that's tough, and those are the little things that people don't think about for police officers when they're out there, and it can be quiet.

1491
02:00:21,373 --> 02:00:24,235
[SPEAKER_17]: I go back, they chose this career and they chose it for a reason, right?

1492
02:00:24,255 --> 02:00:32,559
[SPEAKER_17]: So it's an altruistic type mentality that people who are chosen for this career go out and kind of, you know, they look to help all the time.

1493
02:00:33,120 --> 02:00:35,441
[SPEAKER_17]: Doesn't mean we're not gonna make mistakes, but we're there to help all the time.

1494
02:00:35,461 --> 02:00:36,702
[SPEAKER_17]: We're there to kind of partake in that.

1495
02:00:36,802 --> 02:00:40,624
[SPEAKER_17]: And that when calls for service go up, it's part of the job and they do it.

1496
02:00:41,465 --> 02:00:42,665
[SPEAKER_20]: Gotcha.

