[SPEAKER_17]: there's a sense I can get from reading the reports on like, okay, it's getting busy.

1512
02:01:58,118 --> 02:01:59,579
[SPEAKER_17]: It's around the holiday season, right?

1513
02:01:59,920 --> 02:02:04,824
[SPEAKER_17]: Or it's in, you know, we say after Thanksgiving, it's going to get really busy with certain amount of crimes.

1514
02:02:04,884 --> 02:02:07,566
[SPEAKER_17]: And when I see them, I expect to see them and sort of thing.

1515
02:02:07,586 --> 02:02:08,847
[SPEAKER_17]: And you're like, okay, this is normal.

1516
02:02:09,188 --> 02:02:10,929
[SPEAKER_17]: That's when you see things that you don't expect.

1517
02:02:10,989 --> 02:02:14,632
[SPEAKER_17]: And I know that's a vague type type of answer.

1518
02:02:14,672 --> 02:02:16,094
[SPEAKER_17]: But the other part of it is

1519
02:02:17,368 --> 02:02:24,814
[SPEAKER_17]: you know, the metrics I get are probably a little bit less when somebody responds to social media and says, Hey, listen, thanks for doing this.

1520
02:02:24,894 --> 02:02:25,955
[SPEAKER_17]: I get emails all the time.

1521
02:02:25,995 --> 02:02:29,417
[SPEAKER_17]: You know, I bumped, you know, officer, so-and-so helped me out and did this.

1522
02:02:29,477 --> 02:02:31,859
[SPEAKER_17]: And I get a lot of that and that gives you the metrics.

1523
02:02:31,899 --> 02:02:35,022
[SPEAKER_17]: And I do compare that with, you know, compliances and complaints.

